0January%2020%2C%201981%2C%20on%20the%20day%20Ronald%20Reagan%20took%20over%20as%20the%20new%20US%20president%2C%20Iran%20freed%2052%20American%20hostages%20it%20had%20been%20holding%20for%20over%20a%20year.%20That%20projected%20Reagan%20as%20a%20strong%20leader%20sending%20a%20powerful%20signal%20to%20US%20allies%20and%20its%20foes.%20His%20predecessor%2C%20Jimmy%20Carter%2C%20did%20all%20the%20negotiations%20and%20tried%20his%20best%20to%20have%20the%20hostages%20released%20while%20he%20was%20still%20the%20president.%20But%20Tehran%20would%20not%20let%20him%20take%20the%20glory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForty-four%20years%20on%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20taking%20the%20credit%20for%20the%20Gaza%20ceasefire%20deal%2C%20which%20will%20come%20into%20effect%20a%20day%20before%20his%20inauguration%2C%20cementing%20his%20reputation%20as%20a%20tough%20leader.%20Biden%20can%20say%20that%20the%20deal%20happened%20under%20his%20watch.%20But%20there%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20it%20was%20Trump%20whose%20pressure%20led%20to%20achieve%20the%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20declared%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%20Truth%20Social%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20EPIC%20ceasefire%20agreement%20could%20have%20only%20happened%20as%20a%20result%20of%20our%20Historic%20Victory%20in%20November%2C%20as%20it%20signalled%20to%20the%20entire%20World%20that%20my%20Administration%20would%20seek%20Peace%20and%20negotiate%20deals%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20of%20all%20Americans%2C%20and%20our%20Allies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDays%20after%20he%20threatened%20that%20there%20better%20be%20a%20Gaza%20deal%20by%20his%20January%2020%20inauguration%20or%20%E2%80%9Call%20hell%20would%20break%20out%E2%80%9D%2C%20his%20special%20envoy%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Steven%20Witkoff%2C%20landed%20in%20Tel%20Aviv%20last%20Saturday.%20It%20was%20the%20Sabbath%2C%20the%20day%20of%20rest%20for%20Jews.%20But%20Witkoff%20insisted%20on%20meeting%20the%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20that%20day.%20At%20their%20meeting%2C%20he%20conveyed%20Trump's%20message%20that%20the%20incoming%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%20wanted%20to%20end%20the%20Gaza%20war%20and%20demanded%20that%20a%20ceasefire%20agreement%20be%20signed%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20format%20of%20the%20three-stage%20deal%20announced%20on%20Wednesday%20was%20proposed%20by%20Biden%20in%20May%20last%20year%20and%20was%20later%20also%20endorsed%20by%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council.%20But%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%20kept%20dragging%20the%20negotiations%20over%20it.%20In%20Isreal%2C%20Netanyahu%20refused%20to%20give%20any%20concessions%20to%20Hamas%20and%20continued%20with%20his%20brute%20military%20operation%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20right-wing%20parties%20in%20Israel's%20ruling%20coalition%20also%20threatened%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20Netanyahu%20government%20if%20he%20agreed%20to%20a%20ceasefire%20deal.%20Indeed%2C%20one%20right-wing%20leader%2C%20Ben%20Gvir%2C%20has%20openly%20admitted%20to%20successfully%20blocking%20previous%20attempts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Surprised%20Israelis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20pressure%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20ceasefire%20has%20come%20as%20a%20shock%20to%20right-wing%20Israelis%2C%20who%20hailed%20his%20election%20victory%20in%20November.%20In%20his%20first%20term%2C%20Trump%20moved%20the%20US%20embassy%20from%20Tel%20Aviv%20to%20Jerusalem%20and%20recognised%20Israel's%20sovereignty%20over%20the%20Golan%20Heights%2C%20a%20Syrian%20territory%20occupied%20by%20Israel%20after%20the%201967%20war%20with%20Arabs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Trump%20announced%20the%20appointment%20of%20an%20Evangelical%20Christian%20Mike%20Huckabee%20as%20his%20ambassador%20to%20Israel%2C%20many%20right-wing%20Israelis%20were%20thrilled%2C%20particularly%20those%20who%20wanted%20new%20Israeli%20settlements%20in%20Gaza.%20Huckabee%20is%20on%20record%20saying%20there%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20the%20West%20Bank%20or%20the%20occupation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20why%20has%20Trump%20pushed%20for%20the%20ceasefire%3F%20Apart%20from%20taking%20credit%20for%20ending%20one%20of%20the%20most%20brutal%20wars%20in%20recent%20history%2C%20Trump%20may%20like%20to%20focus%20on%20larger%20issues%2C%20like%20relations%20with%20China%20and%20ending%20the%20Russia-Ukrainian%20conflict.%20In%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20he%20wants%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20recognise%20Israel%2C%20which%20will%20be%20a%20huge%20achievement%20of%20his%20administration.%20With%20the%20continuing%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20terrible%20sufferings%20of%20Palestinians%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Israel%2C%20Saudis%20could%20not%20afford%20to%20consider%20having%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20is%20unpredictable%2C%20which%20is%20also%20a%20reason%20for%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%20to%20accept%20the%20ceasefire%20deal.%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Qatar%E2%80%94the%20host%20of%20ceasefire%20negotiations%E2%80%94pressured%20Hamas%20to%20accept%20the%20agreement.%20And%20while%20Netanyahu%C2%A0may%20have%20defied%20Biden%20for%20so%20long%2C%20he%20could%20not%20do%20the%20same%20to%20Trump%20and%20must%20keep%20him%20on%20his%20side.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20on%20Sunday%2C%20January%2019%2C%20the%20ceasefire%20will%20last%2042%20days.%20It%20will%20see%20the%20exchange%20of%2033%20Israeli%20hostages%20detained%20by%20Hamas%20and%20Palestinians%20held%20in%20Israeli%20prisons.%20The%20deal%20will%20also%20enable%20the%20return%20of%20displaced%20people%20in%20Gaza%20to%20return%20to%20whatever%20is%20left%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20and%20daily%20delivery%20of%20food%20and%20other%20supplies%20by%20hundreds%20of%20trucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Huge%20Challenge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20things%20can%20still%20go%20wrong.%20There%20can%20be%20accidents%20or%20attacks%20from%20either%20side%2C%20which%20could%20break%20the%20truce.%20But%20even%20if%20the%20guns%20in%20Gaza%20do%20go%20silent%20on%20Sunday%20and%20the%20ceasefire%20holds%20for%20its%20intended%20period%2C%20the%20real%20challenge%20will%20come%20in%20the%20second%20stage%20of%20the%20agreement%2C%20when%20negotiations%20for%20ending%20the%20war%20and%20return%20of%20all%20remaining%20hostages%20would%20begin.%20Is%20Israel%20ready%20for%20a%20permanent%20end%20to%20the%20war%3F%20And%20what%20will%20stop%20a%20Palestinian%20activist%20from%20firing%20at%20Israel%2C%20given%20the%20bitterness%20in%20the%20community%20after%20Israel's%20campaign%3F%C2%A0There%20is%20not%20a%20single%20Palestinian%20left%20in%20Gaza%20who%20has%20not%20lost%20a%20friend%20or%20relative%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Israel%20in%20this%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20and%20final%20phase%20will%20involve%20the%20reconstruction%20of%20Gaza%2C%20whose%20infrastructure%20has%20been%20destroyed%20by%20the%20Israeli%20bombardments.%20The%20Arab%20countries%20that%20funded%20reconstruction%20in%20the%20past%20will%20be%20reluctant%20to%20do%20it%20this%20time%20unless%20they%20are%20sure%20that%20Israel%20will%20not%20destroy%20it%20again.%20It%20is%20also%20not%20clear%20who%20will%20govern%20Gaza%20now%2C%20as%20Hamas%2C%20even%20in%20its%20much-weakened%20form%2C%20will%20be%20unacceptable%20to%20both%20Israel%20and%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20Trump%20will%20react%20in%20the%20second%20and%20third%20phases%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20predict%20given%20his%20nature.%20In%20office%2C%20he%20may%20act%20differently.%20But%20both%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20know%20that%20things%20have%20dramatically%20changed%20over%20the%20past%2015%20months%20when%20the%20current%20war%20began%20with%20the%20attack%20on%20Israel%20by%20the%20militant%20group%20on%20October%207%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20military%20response%20was%20swift%20and%20massive.%20One%20by%20one%2C%20it%20eliminated%20all%20the%20top%20leaders%20of%20Hamas%20and%20its%20ally%20Hezbollah%20and%20destroyed%20their%20military%20infrastructure.%20This%20also%20led%20to%20a%20regime%20change%20in%20Syria%2C%20where%20Bashar%20Assad%20was%20forced%20to%20flee%20the%20country%20and%20seek%20refuge%20in%20Russia.%20Hezbollah's%20primary%20backer%2C%20Iran%2C%20has%20also%20been%20weakened%20following%20Assad's%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Cost%20Of%20Israel's%20Military%20Response%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20may%20have%20succeeded%20in%20decapitating%20the%20leadership%20of%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20and%20destroying%20their%20war%20machines.%20But%20the%20human%20cost%20of%20its%20military%20response%20in%20Gaza%20has%20also%20hit%20its%20international%20image%20and%20sparked%20a%20global%20outcry.%20Its%20brutal%20military%20campaign%20killed%20over%2047%2C000%20people%20in%20Gaza%2C%20displaced%20most%20of%20its%202.3%20million%20population%20and%20destroyed%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20residential%20buildings.%20Most%20of%20the%20victims%20have%20been%20innocent%20civilians%20who%20are%20now%20living%20in%20famine-like%20conditions%2C%20with%20hardly%20any%20access%20to%20health%2C%20food%2C%20clean%20water%20or%20proper%20shelter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Israel%20has%20faced%20genocide%20accusations%20at%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice.%20The%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20even%20issued%20arrest%20warrants%20against%20Netanyahu%20and%20his%20former%20defence%20minister%20on%20charges%20of%20war%20crimes%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20successful%20ceasefire%20may%20bring%20an%20immediate%20end%20to%20the%20sufferings%20of%20Gaza's%20population%2C%20and%20the%20end%20of%20the%20current%20war%20may%20achieve%20a%20little%20more.%20But%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20the%20end%20of%20the%20wider%20conflict%20between%20Palestinians%20and%20Israel.%20While%20the%20Gaza%20war%20raged%20on%2C